00:01:25.370 --> 00:01:26.170 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:01:26.170 --> 00:01:29.530 align:middle line:84%
>> So would you share a little
bit about your journey with us

00:01:29.530 --> 00:01:33.130 align:middle line:90%
and just where it began?

00:01:33.130 --> 00:01:34.390 align:middle line:90%
>> Sure, sure.

00:01:34.390 --> 00:01:38.470 align:middle line:84%
Well, I'm almost 40 and I
was born in the Philippines.

00:01:38.470 --> 00:01:41.890 align:middle line:84%
At 11 years old, I came
from the Philippines

00:01:41.890 --> 00:01:46.870 align:middle line:84%
to Australia on my own because
my mother and father separated,

00:01:46.870 --> 00:01:49.150 align:middle line:84%
and my mother couldn't
come to pick me up

00:01:49.150 --> 00:01:53.260 align:middle line:84%
in the Philippines
because of papers that

00:01:53.260 --> 00:01:54.630 align:middle line:90%
just wasn't happening yet.

00:01:54.630 --> 00:01:59.950 align:middle line:84%
My-- her husband at that
time that's Australian died.

00:01:59.950 --> 00:02:02.830 align:middle line:84%
So I had to come
from the Philippines

00:02:02.830 --> 00:02:06.280 align:middle line:84%
on the plane for nine
hours on my own at 11.

00:02:06.280 --> 00:02:07.780 align:middle line:90%
It was petrifying.

00:02:07.780 --> 00:02:14.445 align:middle line:84%
And then I came to Australia
and it wasn't the best childhood

00:02:14.445 --> 00:02:16.570 align:middle line:84%
because my mother was going
through a lot of issues

00:02:16.570 --> 00:02:18.130 align:middle line:90%
back at that time.

00:02:18.130 --> 00:02:22.450 align:middle line:84%
And there you have it, at
13-year-old I was already

00:02:22.450 --> 00:02:27.620 align:middle line:84%
taking meth and hanging with
the wrong crowd, drinking and--

00:02:27.620 --> 00:02:28.420 align:middle line:90%
yeah.

00:02:28.420 --> 00:02:33.040 align:middle line:84%
So it just kind of went
downhill from there.

00:02:33.040 --> 00:02:36.200 align:middle line:84%
And at 14 years old I was
sent back to the Philippines

00:02:36.200 --> 00:02:39.507 align:middle line:84%
and I was getting heavier and
heavier into my shabu, or meth

00:02:39.507 --> 00:02:45.050 align:middle line:84%
use, and somehow when I
was in the Philippines,

00:02:45.050 --> 00:02:48.700 align:middle line:84%
my dad had a friend that
owned a travel agency.

00:02:48.700 --> 00:02:52.150 align:middle line:84%
So he got me working
there at 14 years old.

00:02:52.150 --> 00:02:55.630 align:middle line:84%
And because I was so
bubbly and personable,

00:02:55.630 --> 00:02:58.030 align:middle line:84%
I sold the most
travels to Australia

00:02:58.030 --> 00:02:59.860 align:middle line:84%
because I just came
from Australia.

00:02:59.860 --> 00:03:01.180 align:middle line:90%
And

00:03:01.180 --> 00:03:04.330 align:middle line:84%
I was able to save for
my ticket from Manila

00:03:04.330 --> 00:03:07.870 align:middle line:84%
to Australia by the
time I turned 15.

00:03:07.870 --> 00:03:13.270 align:middle line:84%
Because at 15 years old,
it was 75% off the ticket

00:03:13.270 --> 00:03:15.070 align:middle line:84%
because I worked
in a travel agency.

00:03:15.070 --> 00:03:19.250 align:middle line:84%
So next thing you know, I was on
the plane back from Australia--

00:03:19.250 --> 00:03:22.750 align:middle line:84%
from Philippines back
to Australia on my own.

00:03:22.750 --> 00:03:25.900 align:middle line:84%
Because at that time, my mother
just won't talk to me anymore

00:03:25.900 --> 00:03:29.753 align:middle line:84%
and Philippines is just too poor
a country for me to really make

00:03:29.753 --> 00:03:30.670 align:middle line:90%
something of it there.

00:03:30.670 --> 00:03:34.580 align:middle line:84%
Because we just-- we'll
give you an example.

00:03:34.580 --> 00:03:38.770 align:middle line:84%
We lived in a place where
we're paying about $100 a month

00:03:38.770 --> 00:03:40.550 align:middle line:84%
and there were eight
people living there.

00:03:40.550 --> 00:03:46.660 align:middle line:84%
So you can imagine what type
of a place it is in Makati.

00:03:46.660 --> 00:03:49.360 align:middle line:84%
So that wasn't a future for
me, so I came to Australia.

00:03:49.360 --> 00:03:51.670 align:middle line:84%
And it just-- it's like
one of those things

00:03:51.670 --> 00:03:54.010 align:middle line:84%
that just keeps getting
worse and worse and worse.

00:03:54.010 --> 00:03:57.220 align:middle line:84%
Even if I was in Australia,
I had no parents.

00:03:57.220 --> 00:03:59.920 align:middle line:84%
No one telling me
not to do anything.

00:03:59.920 --> 00:04:01.915 align:middle line:84%
No one telling me what
right and wrong is.

00:04:01.915 --> 00:04:02.715 align:middle line:90%
>> No boundaries.

00:04:02.715 --> 00:04:04.340 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, god, no.

00:04:04.340 --> 00:04:09.440 align:middle line:84%
And have-- having my mom
rejected me at that time.

00:04:09.440 --> 00:04:14.030 align:middle line:84%
So you can imagine in our teens
we had such low self-esteem

00:04:14.030 --> 00:04:14.830 align:middle line:90%
issues, right?

00:04:14.830 --> 00:04:19.510 align:middle line:84%
Well, mine was like 20 times
lower self-esteem than most.

00:04:19.510 --> 00:04:22.460 align:middle line:84%
So it wasn't long
before I was 18

00:04:22.460 --> 00:04:24.670 align:middle line:84%
and I was already
working in an agency,

00:04:24.670 --> 00:04:28.590 align:middle line:84%
selling my body for the
drugs that I was using.

00:04:28.590 --> 00:04:34.990 align:middle line:84%
And, yeah, so got involved
with many Yakuza and Triad,

00:04:34.990 --> 00:04:36.760 align:middle line:90%
those types of people.

00:04:36.760 --> 00:04:42.880 align:middle line:84%
And I went to Japan to
hostess is what you call that.

00:04:42.880 --> 00:04:44.650 align:middle line:84%
But actually, I went
there as a model.

00:04:44.650 --> 00:04:48.400 align:middle line:84%
And then when I got there, I
decided that all the models

00:04:48.400 --> 00:04:50.800 align:middle line:84%
there would do work
at night, which

00:04:50.800 --> 00:04:52.960 align:middle line:90%
is what the hostess thing was.

00:04:52.960 --> 00:04:54.760 align:middle line:84%
So I did that for
a long time and got

00:04:54.760 --> 00:04:56.940 align:middle line:84%
involved with the
Yakuza and Triad people.

00:04:56.940 --> 00:04:59.620 align:middle line:84%
And just for a good 10
years I was using meth

00:04:59.620 --> 00:05:01.810 align:middle line:90%
and Coke and all the drugs.

00:05:01.810 --> 00:05:06.700 align:middle line:84%
And anxiety issues,
I was always so--

00:05:06.700 --> 00:05:07.780 align:middle line:90%
just the palpitations.

00:05:07.780 --> 00:05:09.698 align:middle line:84%
I was so scared
because I didn't know

00:05:09.698 --> 00:05:10.990 align:middle line:90%
who's going to take care of me.

00:05:10.990 --> 00:05:12.532 align:middle line:84%
I didn't know how
I was going to eat.

00:05:12.532 --> 00:05:13.570 align:middle line:90%
What am I going to do.

00:05:13.570 --> 00:05:16.210 align:middle line:90%
I lived no where.

00:05:16.210 --> 00:05:18.160 align:middle line:84%
Just off the-- the
clothes off my back.

00:05:18.160 --> 00:05:20.860 align:middle line:90%
And at 23 got bipolar.

00:05:20.860 --> 00:05:23.260 align:middle line:84%
My mom wanted to speak
to me, so she invited

00:05:23.260 --> 00:05:24.400 align:middle line:90%
me to go back to Australia.

00:05:24.400 --> 00:05:27.970 align:middle line:90%
When I first saw her, all the--

00:05:27.970 --> 00:05:32.320 align:middle line:84%
gosh, all the fear and all
the kind of feeling of,

00:05:32.320 --> 00:05:35.050 align:middle line:84%
you didn't take care of me,
just smacked me in the face

00:05:35.050 --> 00:05:36.010 align:middle line:90%
and I got ill.

00:05:36.010 --> 00:05:40.900 align:middle line:84%
I got psychotic and I went
to Toowoomba Base Hospital

00:05:40.900 --> 00:05:43.660 align:middle line:84%
and I was institutionalized
for three whole months.

00:05:43.660 --> 00:05:48.070 align:middle line:84%
>> So, Maria, when you spent
time in the institution,

00:05:48.070 --> 00:05:51.760 align:middle line:84%
when you were institutionalized
for that three month period,

00:05:51.760 --> 00:05:54.910 align:middle line:84%
was that your first time
that you had actually weaned

00:05:54.910 --> 00:05:57.430 align:middle line:84%
yourself off the various
substances over the seven years

00:05:57.430 --> 00:05:59.360 align:middle line:90%
that you had been addicted to?

00:05:59.360 --> 00:06:02.410 align:middle line:84%
>> Gosh, that's a
question and a half.

00:06:02.410 --> 00:06:05.830 align:middle line:90%
It-- my addiction is--

00:06:05.830 --> 00:06:08.500 align:middle line:84%
it's just a constant
underlying current

00:06:08.500 --> 00:06:10.330 align:middle line:90%
that happened in my life.

00:06:10.330 --> 00:06:15.150 align:middle line:84%
It wasn't-- well, I'd like to
say it didn't really ruin me.

00:06:15.150 --> 00:06:18.690 align:middle line:90%
But looking back, it really did.

00:06:18.690 --> 00:06:22.060 align:middle line:84%
When I would take Coke,
it'll be for a whole weekend.

00:06:22.060 --> 00:06:27.710 align:middle line:84%
If I got on the methamphetamine,
it'll be for weeks at a time.

00:06:27.710 --> 00:06:28.960 align:middle line:90%
If I go clubbing--

00:06:28.960 --> 00:06:32.200 align:middle line:84%
I was a nightclub girl, so
Thursday, Friday, Saturday

00:06:32.200 --> 00:06:34.120 align:middle line:84%
night we'd just be
drinking all night.

00:06:34.120 --> 00:06:37.900 align:middle line:84%
So I haven't really
thought to myself

00:06:37.900 --> 00:06:41.170 align:middle line:84%
prior to getting sick
or institutionalized

00:06:41.170 --> 00:06:42.760 align:middle line:90%
that I need to stop.

00:06:42.760 --> 00:06:46.600 align:middle line:84%
It was still too new,
even if it started at 13.

00:06:46.600 --> 00:06:48.620 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, I just didn't
think it was problematic.

00:06:48.620 --> 00:06:52.540 align:middle line:84%
So, yeah, it really was the
first time that I stopped.

00:06:52.540 --> 00:06:54.970 align:middle line:84%
>> So you spent
three months in a--

00:06:54.970 --> 00:06:56.390 align:middle line:90%
being in an asylum.

00:06:56.390 --> 00:06:57.190 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:06:57.190 --> 00:06:58.590 align:middle line:90%
>> What occurred then?

00:06:58.590 --> 00:07:01.891 align:middle line:84%
What followed after
those three months?

00:07:01.891 --> 00:07:04.240 align:middle line:84%
>> You wouldn't believe
it, but that was--

00:07:04.240 --> 00:07:10.270 align:middle line:84%
after I was released, I actually
had my first suicide attempt,

00:07:10.270 --> 00:07:15.970 align:middle line:84%
because it's a crippling
feeling when you're young

00:07:15.970 --> 00:07:18.430 align:middle line:84%
and you think you've got
your whole life ahead of you

00:07:18.430 --> 00:07:21.100 align:middle line:84%
and you think you're
pretty and you think you've

00:07:21.100 --> 00:07:25.630 align:middle line:84%
got a control on
men, that you're now

00:07:25.630 --> 00:07:28.930 align:middle line:84%
bipolar or
schizophreniform disorder

00:07:28.930 --> 00:07:30.400 align:middle line:90%
is what they called it.

00:07:30.400 --> 00:07:34.740 align:middle line:84%
And they say you can
see if you can do drugs.

00:07:34.740 --> 00:07:36.280 align:middle line:84%
I don't recommend
it, but because

00:07:36.280 --> 00:07:42.670 align:middle line:84%
of your systems in your head,
you get high quite easily.

00:07:42.670 --> 00:07:44.080 align:middle line:90%
It's really detrimental to you.

00:07:44.080 --> 00:07:45.880 align:middle line:90%
So I was like, that's it.

00:07:45.880 --> 00:07:50.020 align:middle line:84%
If I can't escape from the pain
of being rejected and being

00:07:50.020 --> 00:07:52.360 align:middle line:84%
alone and really having
no one to go back to,

00:07:52.360 --> 00:07:55.330 align:middle line:84%
then I really don't
want this life anymore.

00:07:55.330 --> 00:07:59.560 align:middle line:84%
And so I was on so many
pills so I drank it all.

00:07:59.560 --> 00:08:01.900 align:middle line:84%
And apparently, my mom
came home from shopping

00:08:01.900 --> 00:08:03.700 align:middle line:84%
because she was
doing her shopping

00:08:03.700 --> 00:08:05.680 align:middle line:90%
and she just had a really--

00:08:05.680 --> 00:08:08.710 align:middle line:84%
feeling inside her so she
went home straight away,

00:08:08.710 --> 00:08:12.280 align:middle line:84%
found me overdosed, and
went and got hospitalized.

00:08:12.280 --> 00:08:15.822 align:middle line:84%
So it's funny how you picked
up like, you were saying what

00:08:15.822 --> 00:08:17.030 align:middle line:90%
happened straight after that?

00:08:17.030 --> 00:08:18.600 align:middle line:90%
Well, that's what happened.

00:08:18.600 --> 00:08:19.400 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:08:19.400 --> 00:08:20.200 align:middle line:90%
>> Wow.

00:08:20.200 --> 00:08:24.820 align:middle line:84%
And so was it the one attempt,
or did you try multiple times?

00:08:24.820 --> 00:08:27.820 align:middle line:84%
>> There were a few
more times after that.

00:08:27.820 --> 00:08:32.510 align:middle line:84%
One other time was
when I was at Uni.

00:08:32.510 --> 00:08:33.590 align:middle line:90%
I was trying so hard.

00:08:33.590 --> 00:08:36.429 align:middle line:84%
But for some reason, I just
felt like I was different.

00:08:36.429 --> 00:08:39.730 align:middle line:84%
And I was getting
disability support pension

00:08:39.730 --> 00:08:40.820 align:middle line:90%
